Test utility design rationale:
- Platform detection critical for workshop success across environments
- Mock clients enable offline development and consistent testing
- Configurable latency simulates real-world conditions
- Cost tracking in mocks teaches financial awareness early

Platform considerations tested:
- macOS ARM64: Fast but may have different tool availability
- Linux ARM64 (RPi): Resource constrained, needs conservative limits
- FreeBSD: Docker unavailable, different networking stack
- Replit: Severe resource limits, no Docker, shared environment
- Codespaces: Container networking, different service names

Mock design principles:
- Realistic response patterns based on actual LLM behavior
- Failure injection for teaching error handling
- State tracking for debugging student code
- Performance characteristics match production services
